Thanks,B  I turned the engine so the notch on the pulley was at 0, both valves
free on number 1 and the rotor was then point at 730- 8 o'clock.B  I turned
the case of the distributor (009) so the notch is also there and rearranged
the plug wires .B  Was able to start the bus and adjust the timing, although
my timing light showed it to be way advanced.B  I'll look at it again next
weekend. B  Thanks everybody for the advice.

