Does the bus run? B If so I would simply ensure the timing and dwell are set
correctly and drive it. B The risk involved with potentially dropping a shim
washer for the drive is likely greater than just wanting to align the
distributor correctly.




Jason





When I turn the engine so that the distributor drive shaft is approximately at
the 12 degree offset shown in Bentley, the notch on the crank pulley is ~180
degrees off, not at zero like it should be.B B Is it possible for the
distributor drive shaft to be installed wrong?B B I would note that the notch
in the distributor case was not in the place it should have been either.
